Name: Romance: an Affair with...

ChangeDescriptionText: 0|For now, your affair with your officer is forgotten.~1|You have fraternised with one of your officers.
Description: You have engaged in a liaison with one of your officers, out at zee.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have been fraternising with one of your officers.
Name: Romance: Love in the Dark

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have a sweetheart in London.~0|They're gone.~100|You had a sweetheart in London
Description: You chose a sweetheart in Fallen London.
Name: Romance: Someone Back Home

Description: All the adventures of the heart are here, in prose, poetry or pictorial form. Some may be more suitable for private consumption. [Note: in London, customs duty is paid on love stories. Even illustrated love stories.]
Name: Romantic Literature

ChangeDescriptionText: 10|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of sharp chocolate.~1|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of mild coffee.~20|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of burnt rope.~30|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of winter wind.~40|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of hot pitch.~50|Cultivating a bitter flavour: the taste of brimstone.
Description: To ignite the mind.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Mild coffee~10|Sharp chocolate~20|Burnt rope~30|Winter wind~40|Hot pitch~50|Brimstone
Name: Rosegate: The Bitter Flavour

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have agreed to transport the Dogged Apprentice to the Grand Geode.
Description: His master went far in pursuit of a cigar.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|A dejected youth, headed for the Grand Geode~2|A recovering youth, headed for the Grand Geode
Name: Rosegate: The Dogged Apprentice

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have agreed to take the Dogged Apprentice to Rosegate.~10|The Crotchety Tobacconist would like you to aid in the creation of his underwater cigar.~15|The cigar is nearly complete.~20|You dashed the hopes of the Crotchety Tobacconist ever creating his underwater cigar.~45|You have agreed to deliver the Crotchety Tobacconist to the Iron Republic.~50|You have dropped off the Crotchety Tobacconist, to begin mass production of his underwater cigars.~25|You have agreed to deliver the Crotchety Tobacconist to the Iron Republic.~40|You aided the Crotchety Tobacconist in creating the underwater cigar.	~30|The Crotchety Tobacconist will wallow within the Iron Republic.
Description: Everyone has a dream.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You are delivering the Dogged Apprentice and his rumbling crate to Rosegate~15|The cigar is nearly complete~10|You are assisting in the realisation of an underwater cigar~25|You are delivering the Crotchety Tobacconist to the Iron Republic~45|You are delivering the Crotchety Tobacconist to the Iron Republic~50|The Crotchety Tobacconist will mass produce his underwater cigar in the Iron Republic~30|The Crotchety Tobacconist will wallow within the Iron Republic~20|You dashed the hopes of the Crotchety Tobacconist ever creating his underwater cigar~40|You aided the Crotchety Tobacconist in creating the underwater cigar
Name: Rosegate: The Fate of a Cigar

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Dogged Apprentice has been harvested.~2|You have been harvested.~3|The cigar has been destroyed.
Description: A cigar is nothing without its wrapper.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|A taste of hate~2|A taste of passion~3|Obliteration
Name: Rosegate: The Final Flavour

ChangeDescriptionText: 10|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of an apple slice.~30|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of a Surface rose.~40|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of a Viennese greenhouse.~50|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of a beloved's perfume.~20|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of a fresh-baked pie.~1|Cultivating a luscious flavour: the taste of a stale pastry.
Description: To burn.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|A stale pastry~10|An apple slice~30|A Surface rose~40|A Viennese greenhouse~50|A beloved's perfume~20|A fresh-baked pie
Name: Rosegate: The Luscious Flavour

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of kettle steam.~10|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of watery beer.~20|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of marrow broth.~30|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of well-aged wine.~40|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of warm blood.~50|Cultivating a robust flavour: the taste of fecund earth.
Description: To sustain.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Kettle steam~10|Watery beer~20|Marrow broth~30|Well-aged wine~40|Warm blood~50|Fecund earth
Name: Rosegate: The Robust Flavour

Description: Every second of every minute; hour; day; week; month; year; is an agony to him.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|He won't wait forever~16|He can wait no longer
Name: Rosegate: The Tobacconist's Impatience

AvailableAt: Hunt Blue Prophets or Milliner-Bats to find these.
Description: Light as a thought, and jewel-bright
Name: Royal-Blue Feather

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Bound for both the Cumaean Canal and the Iron and Misery Co. Funging Station.~3|There is still one port left to visit.~5|Ready to visit the chess tournament in Port Cecil.~10|The immortal man is dead!~100|You have refused to carry him farther.~15|Bound for Kingeater's Castle.~20|A promise of liberty, equality, and eternity.~50|He's on his own.
Description: The Gnomic Gallivant is on a mission. "The board will forever alter," he says.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Bound for both the Cumaean Canal and the Iron and Misery Co. Funging Station~3|There is still one port left to visit~5|Ready to visit the chess tournament in Port Cecil~10|The immortal man is dead!	~100|You refused to carry the Gnomic Gallivant any farther after he set off a bomb at the chess tournament~20|The Gnomic Gallivant spoke to an invisible master. You have been promised liberty, equality, and eternity~15|Bound for Kingeater's Castle~50|You refused to help the Gnomic Gallivant with his plot.
Name: Ruby Writing

Description: The pirates of Gaider's Mourn tell many tales of this clay corsair.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|The Pirate-Poet is roaming the zee~5|The Pirate-Poet is being hunted~6|The Pirate-Poet is not currently at zee~99|The Pirate-Poet is believed dead~90|The Pirate-Poet is said to be lost at zee~10|The Pirate-Poet is believed to be a prisoner
Name: Rumours of the Pirate-Poet

Description: All the fire of Hell, and all the aroma of Heaven.
Name: Sack of Darkdrop Coffee Beans

Description: How much of yourself can you give before there is nothing left to take?
Name: Sacks and Snow: A Chill Presence

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Snow Child is starting to thaw.~2|The Snow Child is beginning to melt.~3|The Snow Child is struggling.~4|The Snow Child fights to stay together.~40|The Snow Child will no longer melt.~40|The Snow Child has melted.
Description: It is in its nature to melt.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Snow Child is well-frozen by the chill of the North~2|The Snow Child has begun to thaw~3|The Snow Child leaves puddles where it walks~4|The Snow Child has little time left~40|The Snow Child is stable~99|The Snow Child has melted
Name: Sacks and Snow: Heart of Snow

ChangeDescriptionText: 20|You are in the Service of Mr Sacks.~10|You turned away Mr Sacks. Nothing bad can possibly come of this.~30|You have been given your first delivery.~39|You have completed your first delivery.~40|You have been given your second delivery.~49|You have completed your second delivery.~50|You have been given your third delivery.~70|Your service is concluded.~99|You bought your way out of Service.
Description: Take too much time and he may take you.
LevelDescriptionText: 20|Mr Sacks has taken your Service~10|You turned away Mr Sacks~39|You have made your first delivery for Mr Sacks~49|You have made your second delivery for Mr Sacks~50|Mr Sacks requires passage to the Avid Horizon~70|Something awaits you in your Lodgings~80|Your service to Mr Sacks is concluded~99|You bought your way out of Service~40|You must deliver a jewelled bird to the Isle of Cats or Mutton Island~30|You must deliver hunger to Khan's Heart or Pigmote Isle
Name: Sacks and Snow: In the Service of Mr Sacks

ChangeDescriptionText: 2|You have named the Snow Child
LevelDescriptionText: 2|Chione~3|Loki~4|Boreas~5|Winter~6|Snegurochka~7|Elliot~8|Rose~1|Snow Child
Name: Sacks and Snow: The Snow Child's Name

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have created a snow child.~2|You spoke to the Snow Child.~7|The Snow Child has made a wish.~10|You know how to help the Snow Child.~20|The Snow Child is complete.~99|The Snow Child is no more.~5|The Snow Child has joined the ship.~80|The Snow Child's real story has begun.~88|You abandoned the Snow Child.
Description: A child of snow was born at the Avid Horizon.
LevelDescriptionText: 5|You have named the Snow Child~2|You have spoken to the Snow Child~20|The Snow Child will head East from Irem~1|You have helped create a snow child~7|The Snow Child wants to go East - if you can stop it melting~10|You have learned that the Snow Child requires Heartmetal~80|The Snow Child has begun its journey~88|The Snow Child returned home~99|The Snow Child melted
Name: Sacks and Snow: What Snow May Become

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are recovering salvage.~0|Salvage complete!
Name: Salvaging a wreck

Description: It only lasts so long...
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Festival of Silk begins~6|The Festival of Silk draws to a close~2|The Festival of Silk warms up~3|The Festival of Silk fills the island with cheer~4|The Festival of Silk is in full swing~5|The Festival of Silk feels like it will never end~7|The Festival of Silk is ending~8|The Festival of Silk is over
Name: Saviour's Rocks: At the Festival of Silk

Description: If you're lucky, it will only kill you.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Avaricious Lorn-Fluke's Will

Description: You have encountered the grand spider-council of Saviour's Rocks.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|A Stranger to Spiders~99|A Scourge of Spiders~30|A Supplicant of Spiders~90|A Spurner of Spiders~40|A Scavenger for Spiders~50|A Salvager for Spiders~75|A Stooge of Spiders~20|A Supplier to Spiders~10|A Supplier of Tomb Colonists to Spiders?
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Caught in the webs of Saviour's Rocks

Description: She's not ready for a fight like this!
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Nocturne Integrity

Description: They are always watching. So are you.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Spying on the Sorrow Spiders

Description: Every ship has its secrets.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: The Fate of the Nocturne

Description: Saviour's Rocks gives thanks to its generous neighbours
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Festival of Silk has begun~2|The Festival of Silk is over~5|The Festival of Silk is cancelled~6|The Festival of Silk is cancelled forever
Name: Saviour's Rocks: The Festival of Silk

Description: She's falling apart, but at least she doesn't have far too go.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: The Final Voyage of the Nocturne

Description: Definitely not sorrow-spider eggs. Deliver them to Fallen London.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Trinkets. Just Trinkets.

Description: Waiting for an audience with the spider-council of Saviour's Rocks.
Name: Saviour's Rocks: Walk Into My Parlour, Said...

Description: Coral that glimmers as if moonlit. It makes marvellous jewellery or terribly expensive tea.
Name: Scintillack

Description: Your line will continue. [You have established a dynasty of zee-captains. This will persist between captains, unless something happens to end it.]
Name: Scion

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Lost Pilgrim settles into her bunk with vague contentment as she sails for the Gant Pole
Description: She had a reason for coming to Scrimshander. And she has a reason for travelling to the Gant Pole. She's almost sure of it.
Name: Scrimshander: A Lost Pilgrim

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Monastic Drownie silently boards your ship, due for Scrimshander
Description: A quiet drownie borne for Scrimshander, to dedicate his life to research.
Name: Scrimshander: A Monastic Drownie

ChangeDescriptionText: 40|You've left a part of yourself behind for the ivory tower at Scrimshander~25|You have delivered a traveller from Scrimshander~45|You have delivered a traveller from Scrimshander~20|You've learned enough about history to distrust any one person's interpretation~10|You have been to Scrimshander, the City of Remembrance~60|Some questions will remain forever unanswered by history
Description: Don't say "history" as if there's merely one of them.
LevelDescriptionText: 40|You've left a part of yourself behind for the ivory citadel at Scrimshander.	~20|You've learned enough about history to distrust any one person's interpretation.~10|You have been to Scrimshander, the City of Remembrance.~25|You have delivered a traveller from Scrimshander.~45|You have delivered a traveller from Scrimshander.~60|You have uncovered all of the secrets Scrimshander is willing to offer you.
Name: Scrimshander: A Scholar of Histories

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Scholar of Lost Causes grumbles as he settles into his bunk, ready for the trip to Hideaway
Description: He's seen what people have fought and died for. Now he seeks the ones who survived at Hideaway.
Name: Scrimshander: A Scholar of Lost Causes

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Truth-Hunting Chelonate boards your ship, where she eagerly scans the waves for Scrimshander
Description: An aging hunter borne for Scrimshander, searching for the great tales of her ancestors.
Name: Scrimshander: A Truth-Hunting Chelonate

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have delivered the Cargo of Answers to the Drownies.~2|You have delivered the Cargo of Answers to the Chelonates.~3|You are to deliver the Cargo to the Fathomking.~4|You must return to Scrimshander to report the Fathomking's Judgement.~5|You must return to Scrimshander to report the Fathomking's Judgement.~6|You have settled the history of the Chelonate.~7|You are to accompany a Monk into the Archives in Scrimshander.~10|You have settled the history of the Chelonate.~8|You must return to the Chelonate Chronologist in Scrimshander.~9|You must return to the Chelonate Chronologist in Scrimshander.
Description: You have recovered a box of bone carvings from a wreck. The cargo was intended for delivery to Scrimshander.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You gave the Cargo of Answers to the Drownies~2|You gave the Cargo of Answers to the Chelonates~3|You have accepted a task to go to the Fathomking~5|You counselled the Fathomking to strike the Chelonate from his songs~6|You have settled the history of the Cargo of Answers~7|You are to accompany a monk to the archives~8|You sealed the monk, and the Cargo of Answers, into a forgotten vault~9|You uncovered an alternate history of the Chelonate~10|You have settled the history of the Cargo of Answers~4|You counselled the Fathomking to make public the Chelonate's shameful history
Name: Scrimshander: Delivering a Cargo of Answers

Description: The Chelonate hunters believe history is the result of heroic words and deeds. A wise historian learns from their actions and embraces their heroism.
Name: Scrimshander: History of Heroes

ChangeDescriptionText: 10|You seek ancient knowledge in the Ivory Archives~20|The Drownie Chorus will pay handsomely for what you've uncovered
Description: Heroes come and go, cast up by turbulent times and washed away by the next tide. The Drownie Chorus in Scrimshaw's amphitheatre will pay you handsomely to uncover these patterns from the tales in the Ivory Archives.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Search the Ivory Archives for historical patterns~20|Share the patterns of history you've found with the Drownie Chorus in Scrimshander's amphitheatre
Name: Scrimshander: Ivory Archives: Context of Change

Description: They say the Ivory Archives contains stories going back to the start of history. But they aren't very clear on when that was.
Name: Scrimshander: Ivory Archives: Delving into the Past

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You remember fine tea and conversation in the depths of the Ivory Archives~2|You've uncovered the deepest history of Scrimshander
Description: Found something interesting in the Ivory Archives, have you?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You've found who lives in the depths of the archives.~2|You've found Scrimshander's first skeleton, and the history of the tower itself.
Name: Scrimshander: Ivory Archives: Historical Revelations

ChangeDescriptionText: 10|You seek a hero's tale in the Ivory Archives~20|The Chelonate's champions will pay handsomely for what you've discovered.
Description: The Chelonate's champions want to put on a play about a great hero. Find them source material in the archives and they'll give you a hero's reward. But a proper one, not an ironically tragic one that they get in the stories.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Uncover the tale of a great hero in the Ivory Archives~20|Share the heroic tale with the Chelonate's champions in Scrimshander's amphitheatre.
Name: Scrimshander: Ivory Archives: Searching for a Hero

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've added a finger to the bones of Scrimshander~4|You've added a handful of fingers to the bones of Scrimshander
Description: One or more of your finger-bones tells your tale in the ivory walls of Scrimshander. Nothing a stuffed glove can't conceal.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have sacrificed one of your fingers to Scrimshander.~2|Some of your fingers now decorate the city of Scrimshander.~4|You've given Scrimshander a handful of your fingers.
Name: Scrimshander: Missing Finger

Description: Drownie scholars believe that history is a never-ending cycle of trends and social forces. A wise historian learns to sail each era's turbulent tides.
Name: Scrimshander: Tides of Time

Description: The Ivory Archives are jealously guarded. Like most of the figures in the archives, anyone overstaying their welcome is likely to meet a grisly end.
Name: Scrimshander: Time in the Archives

Description: The Chronicler's heart is weary, but his meals are hearty... and he can make soup out of almost anything.
Name: Scrimshaw Chronicler

Description: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks.
Name: Seal of the Red Science

Description: Mysteries are fire. Truth burns.
Name: Searing Enigma

Description: The root of all good. [Discuss Secrets with your Officers to improve your skills. You can speak to your Officers by right-clicking their portraits.]
Name: Secret

Description: Ensure that no-one gets in without the key. In... or out.[This will help protect against acquisitive passengers and over-lively cargo.]
Name: Secure Compartment

Description: Look how it glides. Like moonlight.
Name: Serene Aquarium

Description: He can render the supplies edible, if not palatable.
Name: Shady Cook

Description: A kind of glory.
Name: Shining Knight

Description: A glittering altar carved with the Signs of the South.
Name: Shrine to Stone

Description: More Sigil than man, now. But he sets a true course.
Name: Sigil-Eaten Navigator

AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London, or more reliably at the Shepherd Isles.
Description: Has that tattoo grown since last you looked?
Name: Sigil-Ridden Navigator

Description: Competent? Probably. Trustworthy? Possibly.
Name: Sly Navigator

Description: A monstrous weapon of monstrous heartmetal.
Name: Smith's Anguish

Description: A Miraculous New Process Enables Passage Through Eternal Night! Do Not Consume.  [An adequate device for seeking enemies.]
Name: Soft Glim-Lamp

AvailableAt: This grows in the Wisp-Ways, near the Mangrove College.
Description: In smaller quantities, delightful and refreshing. In larger quantities, one of the very nicest ways to die.
Name: Solacefruit

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The waves are flecked with light.~50|Zee-bats cry out. They are nothing like birds.~39|Something drifts, face-down.~47|A false-star flares in the cavern roof directly above you; flares, and fades.~78|A tiny breeze stirs your hair, and dies.~81|Waves slap the side of the ship. Far below, something moves.~40|Some sort of beetle has invaded your morsel of ship's biscuit. It waggles its antennae impertinently.~20|Green glass and basalt. Salt and silence.~37|The glim-lamp at the prow fizzes, arcs.~30|On the horizon, a sickly yellow light glimmers for a moment, then fades.~49|Where is everyone? Where did they go? ...they're here. They're here. You're not alone.~60|Distant bells.~100|Blue lightnings crawl leisurely up the funnel. "St Erasmus dancing!" the cry goes up.~82|Home. Warmly lit windows, company, peace. Thoughts of home come at the strangest times.~90|The air trembles. A breath of change passes...~25|The glassy chop of dark water. The iron clatter of feet at the hatchway.~10|The air carries the scent of salt and shadows.~43|A zailor raises her head, sniffs sharply. Blood on the wind. ~19|The scent of the zee! Salt and frost and cellars. Black spices.~70|Luminescent beasts like eyeless dolphins play in your wake.~68|A zailor is praying.~74|A sluggish wave. The ship pitches.~84|Far off, very far off, someone screams...~86|Laughter from the fore-deck.~88|A belch of smoke goes up from the funnel.~11|The air trembles. A breath of change passes...~12|A belch of smoke goes up from the funnel.~13|Laughter from the fore-deck.~14|Far off, very far off, someone screams...~85|Zee-bats cry out. They are nothing like birds.~16|A zailor is praying.~17|Luminescent beasts like eyeless dolphins play in your wake.~18|A row of watchful zee-bats perch on the ship's railing. Their heads swivel in unison as you cross the deck.~0|That's all for now.~72|A row of watchful zee-bats hang from a cable. Their heads swivel in unison as you cross the deck.~9|A rock breaks the water like a surfacing zee-beast. No, it's a  zee-beast! No, it's a rock.~3|On the Surface, the sun still warms the Earth. Or so one assumes.~5|A brisk spatter of spray. The Unterzee is restless.~7|An electric shiver to the air. Storm is watching, the zailors would say.~22|The waves are cluttered with zee-wrack, like drowned hair drifting.~51|You are being watched.~52|A soft wind from the East. The impossible scent of pine.~53|Waves slap the side of the ship. Far below, something moves.~54|A ship's horn, far away.~55|Blue lightnings crawl leisurely up the funnel. "St Erasmus dancing!" the cry goes up.~150|You are not welcome here. ~101|Something brushes briefly against the shell. The zub shakes.~110|The brightest light cannot reach this depth. That glow is an illusion. ~120|The air is stale. An off-duty crewman keens softly. ~130|Lights glance past the windows. Another zubmarine?  ~140|The Observation Dome is silent. Your navigator's breath is loud in the stillness.~160|A dull tolling echoes around the bridge. A distress bell, now fading.  ~170|A shoal of fish pass by a porthole. The prow-lamp reveals the midnight iridescence of their scales. ~200|The compass shifts in the binnacle. Briefly, you are off-course. The coral is a useless signpost.~190| A diving-suit floats past the glass.~180|The temperature changes abruptly. Your helmsman complains about goosebumps.
Description: You'll find a story when you next make port. [You'll receive this from time to time as you travel the zee.]
LevelDescriptionText: 0|Nothing awaits you. Time to leave port?~1|Stories await when you next make port.
Name: Something Awaits You

Description: On first sight, it looks like a tomb-colonist coffin. On closer examination, it carries stencilling reading SOOTHE & COOPER and a handwritten tag: 'DELIVERY TO DEPOT (A), STATION III'.
Name: Soothe & Cooper Long-Box

Description: Speculative Consonance: less than a technique, more than just a theory. [The Consonator does not limit your ability to hide.]
Name: Speculative Consonator

Description: The Unmakers have smashed these sad and rubbly remnants off the flanks of a Salt Lion. A contact in London will purchase them.
Name: Sphinxstone

Description: "AN INESCAPABLE ENDING!" A potent weapon which permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Stampshod's 'Calvary' Prong Launcher

Description: Did a Judgement hatch from this grim relic? Or was it something else entirely. Don't look too closely at the eye-hurting absence of colour.
Name: Star-Shell

AvailableAt: The Trade in Long Boxes may lead you to meet new people.
Description: Your work for the Austere Acolyte has introduced you to others on the Island.
Name: Station III: Acquainted with a Heartmetal Smith

Description: Your acquaintance with the Austere Acolyte.
Name: Station III: Earning the Acolyte's Favour

Description: An ingot of silvery metal, dreadfully cold to the touch.
Name: Station III: Heartmetal Ingot

Description: Involvement in a certain trade.
Name: Station III: Trading in Long Boxes

Description: A tool for pragmatic archeologists.
Name: Sticks of Dynamite

Description: It might be some sort of fish, but best not to look too closely.
Name: Strange Catch

Description: My. The Admiralty will certainly want to know this.
Name: Strategic Information

Description: The black bones of zee-monsters make for startling corsets.
Name: Stygian Ivory

Description: Possibly there's a reason you might want to set to zee in a boat the size of a dining-room table. Possibly.
Name: Stymphalos-class Steam Launch

Description: It's very dangerous, but who cares when it's so pretty?
Name: Sunlight-Filled Mirrorcatch Box

Description: Food and equipment. [If you run out of supplies, Hunger will eventually destroy you.]
Name: Supplies

Description: Lenses, tinctures, candles, flammable oils. Now and then, bones.
Name: Supplies for the Work

Description: Ensures your ship's engine won't explode at Full Power.
Name: Suppression

Description: Who rules London's first Unterzee colony?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You are working to protect London's interests in Port Carnelian~2|You have furthered the Khan's interests in port Carnelian~3|You are supporting the tigers' aboriginal claim to Port Carnelian~11|You have ensured Port Carnelian will remain squarely under her Majesty's control~12|You engineered the Khanate's annexation of Port Carnelian~13|You restored the native tigers to power in Port Carnelian
Name: Supremacy: Affairs in Port Carnelian

Description: God bless Her Enduring Majesty, the Empress.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Recovering~5|Renascent~7|Glorious~2|Promising~3|Significant~4|Substantial~6|Tremendous
Name: Supremacy: London

Description: LO THY DREAD EMPIRE CHAOS IS RESTORED LIGHT DIES BEFORE THY UNCREATING WORD
Name: Supremacy: The Anarchists

Description: UN. THE SUN. THE SUN. THE SUN. THE S
LevelDescriptionText: 5|Blazing~7|TRIUMPHANT~4|Burning~3|Radiant~1|Rising~6|Resplendent~2|Gleaming
Name: Supremacy: The Dawn Machine

Description: The Khanate's power is growing.
Name: Supremacy: The Khanate

Description: Patience; rage; patience.
Name: Supremacy: the Lorn-Flukes

Description: The nuns endure.
Name: Surveyed: Abbey Rock

Description: You've seen the blood that flows from the Continent's heart.
Name: Surveyed: Adam's Way

Description: You've seen where the sunlight brushes the zee.
Name: Surveyed: Aestival

AvailableAt: Take a port report at Anthe and then submit it at the Admiralty.
Description: Have you turned in a Port Report of Anthe?
Name: Surveyed: Anthe

Description: You have seen where the world ends. Behind those peaks of ice, something colder by far.
Name: Surveyed: Avid Horizon

Description: You have seen where the Service of the Well is performed.
Name: Surveyed: Chapel of Lights

Description: A caveful of exiles.
Name: Surveyed: Codex

AvailableAt: Provide a Port Report on Dahut to the Admiralty.
Description: You have explored Dahut.
Name: Surveyed: Dahut

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Demeaux Island has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the place where they have more mushrooms than sense.
Name: Surveyed: Demeaux Island

Description: You have returned from the land of soul-stealing monkeys.
Name: Surveyed: Empire of Hands

Description: You have met the squatters at the tower of zee ice.
Name: Surveyed: Frostfound

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Gaider's Mourn has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the lights and the cliffs.
Name: Surveyed: Gaider's Mourn

Description: You have seen the shattered citadel that lies in the zee.
Name: Surveyed: Godfall

Description: You've seen the house of the elect of the Dawn Machine.
Name: Surveyed: Grand Geode

Description: You've made friends with Temtum.
Name: Surveyed: Hideaway

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Hunter's Keep has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office~1|Your visit to Hunter's Keep has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: An odd place. Best to keep an eye on it.
Name: Surveyed: Hunter's Keep

Description: You will return from Irem.
Name: Surveyed: Irem

Description: You have seen the Pirate-King's domain.
Name: Surveyed: Isle of Cats

Description: You've been to Khan's Heart, where the electric lights glow and the clans sharpen their claws.
Name: Surveyed: Khan's Heart

Description: You've seen where the Khanate rebels lair.
Name: Surveyed: Khan's Shadow

Description: You've seen the hungry place at the world's edge.
Name: Surveyed: Kingeater's Castle

AvailableAt: Provide a Port Report on Low Barnet to the Admiralty.
Description: You have explored Low Barnet.
Name: Surveyed: Low Barnet

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Mt Palmerston has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: A detailed report on a place of interest. The Admiralty would value it.
Name: Surveyed: Mt Palmerston

Description: You've been to the great Maw.
Name: Surveyed: Nook

Description: You've seen the Island of Lost Postmen.
Name: Surveyed: Nuncio

Description: You have seen first-hand the Rodent War.
Name: Surveyed: Pigmote Isle

Description: You have seen the city where the Clay Men are made for labour.
Name: Surveyed: Polythreme

Description: Information on Little London for Fallen London.
Name: Surveyed: Port Carnelian

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Port Cecil has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the place where chess is holy.
Name: Surveyed: Port Cecil

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Quaker's Haven has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the hill where the fire is kept.
Name: Surveyed: Quaker's Haven

Description: A place of handmade delights, all available for a price.
Name: Surveyed: Rosegate

Description: You survived a trip to the lair of the sorrow-spiders.
Name: Surveyed: Saviour's Rocks

Description: You've been to the City of Remembrance and left something of yourself behind.
Name: Surveyed: Scrimshander

Description: You can confirm, at least, that they are where they are.
Name: Surveyed: Shepherd Isles

Description: On the very edge of London's influence, curious matters are conducted.
Name: Surveyed: Station III

Description: You've seen the floating corpse of the Turtle.
Name: Surveyed: the Chelonate

Description: You've seen what grows around the Fathomking's throne.
Name: Surveyed: the Fathomking's Hold

Description: You've been where the beasts of the zee go to die.
Name: Surveyed: The Gant Pole

Description: All foison, all abundance.
Name: Surveyed: the Mangrove College

Description: You've seen what happens when one digs too deep for secrets.
Name: Surveyed: the Salt Lions

Description: You've been to the Mother of Fungus.
Name: Surveyed: the Uttershroom

Description: You have found the secluded home of moths and mourning.
Name: Surveyed: Undercrow

Description: There are dark machinations in the walled city of light.
Name: Surveyed: Varchas

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Venderbight has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the place where the half-dead go.
Name: Surveyed: Venderbight

Description: You have seen the isle where one face only is permitted.
Name: Surveyed: Visage

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your visit to Whither has been confirmed by the Admiralty Records Office
Description: You have seen the ice and salt.
Name: Surveyed: Whither

Description: Both secrets and prisoners are locked here.
Name: Surveyed: Wisdom

Description: You have seen the home of sundered hulls.
Name: Surveyed: Wrack

Description: Recall it, then light a candle. Light another.
Name: Tale of Terror!!

Description: The fear of the wide black zee, and the things beyond. [Reduce this with Shore Leave, especially in London. When you return to London after time at zee, your Terror will always drop to 50.]
LevelDescriptionText: 100|Crazed~25|Nervous~50|Fearful~75|Haunted~1|Wary~0|Serene
Name: Terror

Description: This barely qualifies as a book. Dozens of scraps of paper have been crammed into a scuffed folio. Each bears helpful advice on murder, and, often, a stain.
Name: The Boke of Sharpes

Description: It thrums. It wanders. It has a delightful stink. [This ship is available players who backed Sunless Sea at the Navigator Tier or higher. It will become available as DLC at a later date.]
Name: The Cladery Heart

ChangeDescriptionText: 0|Avernus: grey rock and blue water.~1|Naples: crowded streets and the sea's horizon~10|Vienna: revolution in the air
Description: You are far from home.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|Avernus~1|Naples~10|Vienna
Name: The Cruelty of Sunlight

ChangeDescriptionText: 5|Who will the corpse go to?~1|Bound for Hunter's Keep.~10|Bound for Station III.~30|Bound for Nuncio with the Drownie Postman.~15|You witnessed history.~35|Scheduled for redelivery.
Description: It is rare something so awful washes up on shore.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Bound for Hunter's Keep~5|Who will the corpse go to?~10|Bound for Station III with the Anxious University Student~30|Bound for Nuncio with the Drownie Postman~15|You witnessed the Anxious University Student relive history through the needle.~35|You allowed the Drownies to fulfil their concord with the Lorn-Flukes.
Name: The Fate of Needles

Description: Her verses may be complete.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The past has been denied~10|Verse has proven persuasive~20|Authority has been restored~25|A duel has been won~30|The Modiste is triumphant~0|The Poet has been captured
Name: The Fate of the Pirate-Poet

Description: Does her husband survive at the City of Flowers?
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Anthe

Description: Did he seek the City of Peace?
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Dahut

Description: Perhaps he hides in the place where monsters go to die.
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Gant Pole

Description: Did her husband retreat to the City of Refuge?
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Hideaway

Description: Did her husband flee to the City of Freedom?
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Nook
The Fierce Philanthropist: on the Trail

Description: Is her husband at the City of Remembrance?
Name: The Fierce Philanthropist: Scrimshander

Description: This weird skull once adorned the worm-drawn priest-barge of the Chelonate.
Name: The Figurehead of the Eater of Names

Description: "These are the forces that drive the Bazaar." The Impeller runs very, very hot.
Name: The Fulgent Impeller

Description: You don't care for gods, real or imagined. You'll make your own way. [This does not protect you from the curses of the zee-gods.]
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Defiant

Description: It's watching you; if it even exists.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Salt's Attention

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Salt's curse lies on you
Description: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of farewells.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Salt's curse lies on you
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Salt's Curse

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You know something of the three gods of the zee.
Description: There are powers.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Stone, Storm and Salt

Description: It's very far away; but perhaps it's watching you.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Stone's Attention

Description: You carry a curse: the curse of the nameless god of home and healing.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Stone's Curse

Description: An ancient anger knows you.
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Storm's Attention

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Storm's curse lies on you
Description: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of high places and anger.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Storm's curse lies on you
Name: The Gods of the Zee: Storm's Curse

Description: The oldest and deadliest arachnid from its chitinous core. Deadliest, and now thankfully dead.
Name: The Heart of the Tree of Ages

Description: "Herein are recorded certain details of a Voyage through [xxxxx] in the company of [xxxxxx], on [xxxxxx]...." [Use this to increase your Pages. Unless you sell it, future captains will have access to it.]
Name: The Horizon Codex

Description: Now where exactly did you meet, again? Did Clathermont the tattooist introduce you?
Name: The Lady in Lilac

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Last Constable has been seen on Demeaux Island.
Description: Has she found a hiding space amongst the spores?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have not looked for her on Demeaux Island
Name: The Last Constable: Demeaux Island

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Last Constable has been seen in Gaider's Mourn
Description: Is she bringing justice to the pirates of Corsair's Forest?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have not looked for her in Gaider's Mourn
Name: The Last Constable: Gaider's Mourn

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Last Constable has been seen in Khan's Heart.
Description: Could she be hiding out at London's rival?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have not looked for her in Khan's Heart
Name: The Last Constable: Khan's Heart

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are looking for the Last Constable.
Description: You seek her here, you seek her there.
Name: The Last Constable: On The Trail

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Last Constable has been seen in Venderbight.
Description: Is she working amongst the nearly-dead?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have not looked for her in Venderbight
Name: The Last Constable: Venderbight

Description: Old soul. Where are you going, old soul?
Name: The Mark of the East

Description: This is the design he stored in Frostfound.
Name: The Mechanic's Secret

Description: She has no difficulties with blood. But she very much dislikes bloodstains.
Name: The Merciless Modiste

Description: It's not an attractive object. Perhaps you won't keep it on your mantelpiece.
Name: The Merciless Modiste's Heart

Description:
A book for children. One page is devoted to each of the colours of the Neath, which are not found on the Surface.

[Return to the Curator with each of the seven impossible colours in hand. The book's pages give you clues, but you'll need to seek far ports.]
Name: THE NEATHBOW

Description: Legend. Enigma. She has an appointment in Polythreme.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Art has been denied~10|The power of verse~20|Authority is restored~25|A duel has been won~30|The Modiste is triumphant
Name: The Pirate-Poet

Description: He has turned aside from his revenge.
Name: The Prudent Magician

LevelDescriptionText: 2|You carry a wax-paper missive from the Conodont in Nook, to a friend in Anthe~3|You carry a reply from the Conodont's sister.
Name: The respect of the Conodont

Description: He has the quiet smile of a man who has tamped down the earth on his enemy's grave.
Name: The Satisfied Magician

Description: She was the youngest sister of the Hunter's Keep three. Now her home is gone. She will not show her face, nor speak of what occurred, but she is prepared to use her education to help heal your crew...
Name: The Scarred Sister

Description: The place which is no-place held you, crushed you. You carry the wounds still.
Name: The Scars of the North

Description: Sealed with a ribbon. It looks like a ribbon, anyway.
Name: The Scholar's Notes

Description: A shimmering complexus of steel and glass. In its heart, a serpent-king rages. Or so the Magician claims.
Name: The Serpentine

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have brought the Snow Child aboard.~0|The Snow Child has departed.
Description: Every day, it melts a little more.
Name: The Snow Child

Description: The lights of the Elder Continent swim in your blood.
Name: The Touch of the South

Description: Something silver looks out through his eyes.
Name: The Urbane Magician

Description: You have seen behind the Dawn Machine
Name: The Western Stigma

Description: For this, they will all remember you.
Name: The Zong of the Zee

Description: The clock is ticking!
Name: Time Remaining...

AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London, or in a distant port of the North.
Description: Does he ever sleep? His eyes are dark-circled, but his hands are steady.
Name: Tireless Mechanic

Description: Technically, passengers rather than goods. But you'd never know it to talk to them. [They'll pay their passage to the Tomb-Colonies: sell them there.]
Name: Tomb-Colonist

Description: The Monkey Foundling must have dropped it.
Name: Tooth of the Snow Child

Description: In one of the most striking coincidences of our times, torpedoes are 'torpedo-shaped'. [Ammunition for Torpedo Salvoes.]
Name: Torpedo Components

Description: Deploy these in combat for unparalleled protection against torpedoes!
Name: Torpedo Nets

Description: Deployed protection against torpedoes, expressed as %
Name: Torpedo Protection

Description: This determines the effectiveness of torpedo devices. It's only available from device enhancements.
Name: Torpedo Tubes

Description: Each one from a different mouth. [A previous captain in your lineage was a debased cannibal who served the Chapel of Lights and the Drowned Man]
Name: Trophy: A Collection of Teeth

Description: The image of an imposing memorial. The rain-blurred name is difficult to read. [A previous captain in your lineage found and buried their father's bones - or a substitute.]
Name: Trophy: A Daguerreotype of a Memorial

Description: King James' edition, of course. One passage is circled in old red ink - Romans 6:9. [A previous captain in your lineage once achieved immortality, or turned it down.]
Name: Trophy: a Family Bible

Description: The resemblance is obvious. Both are smiling. [A previous captain in your lineage found and rescued their father.]
Name: Trophy: A Family Portrait

Description: An unusual flag from a tiny nation far across the zee.
Name: Trophy: A Folded Flag

Description: The Postmaster Cryptic herself signed this letter. [A previous captain in your lineage found bones in a misaddressed package.]
Name: Trophy: A Letter of Commendation

Description: A zee-monster paperweight, beautifully carved from Stygian ivory. [A previous captain in your lineage proved to be the child of a zee-monster]
Name: Trophy: A Model Monster

Description: The Zociety of Zeafarers took up a collection to have this struck. [A previous captain in your lineage found that their father had sacrificed himself to save his crew.]
Name: Trophy: A Posthumous Medal

Description: The fragments are proudly displayed on a lacquered plaque. [A previous captain in your lineage found bones at Kingeater's Castle]
Name: Trophy: A Shattered Coral Knife

Description: It's a first edition, too. [A captain of your lineage wrote the definitive work of maritime literature.]
Name: Trophy: An Autographed Copy of the Zong of the Zee

Description: Tucked into a desk drawer is a restaurant bill with a triple-circled final total larger than the cost of most ships. [A captain of your lineage won riches and a comfortable retirement.]
Name: Trophy: An Impossible Restaurant Bill

Description: Was this once someone? [A previous captain in your lineage discovered they were part zee-monster, and abandoned their human existence.
Name: Trophy: Not Quite Human

Description: A painting hangs in your study, of a wrought-iron buoy, endlessly afloat, light piercing in the Neath's dark. You can almost hear the bell. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]
Name: Trophy: Restless

Description: A painting hangs in your study. Two travellers watch, forever, as the lights of their destination come closer. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]
Name: Trophy: the Lights of London

Description: A painting hangs in your study, of mist on the face of impossible mountains. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]
Name: Trophy: Those Final Mountains

Description: They make these on the roof-tops, and won't say why. [A one-use item that will remove all Illumination from both sides in combat, and increase Terror.]
Name: Unclear Device

Description: What awaits the Deviless, in the Brass Embassy?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Hell will welcome the Deviless~2|Hell believes the Deviless is a traitor
Name: Uncovering Mysteries: An Infernal Fate

Description: Depths are there for the plumbing. What did the Starved Men leave?
Name: Uncovering Mysteries: the Shattered Citadel

Description: You have access to the Zubmariner DLC expansion.
Name: Under the Unterzee

ChangeDescriptionText: 3|The letter has clearly been opened.~2|No one could tell it's been read. Could they?~1|You've accepted a farewell letter to be delivered to Hideaway.
Description: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, bidding farewell to a lover in Hideaway.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Unopened and pristine~2|Stealthily read~3|Clearly perused
Name: Undercrow: Delivering a Farewell Letter to Hideaway

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have an important letter to deliver.~2|No one will ever know. Right?~3|The letter was open when you got it.
Description: You have an important message to deliver. [Look at the letter in your inventory to see its destination.]
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have an important letter to deliver.~2|You've stealthily read the letter.~3|The letter has clearly been opened.
Name: Undercrow: Delivering a Letter

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've accepted a letter of apology to be delivered to Nook.~2|No one could tell it's been read. Could they?~3|The letter has clearly been opened.
Description: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, apologizing to a comrade in Nook.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Unopened and pristine~2|Stealthily read~3|Clearly perused
Name: Undercrow: Delivering a Letter of Apology to Nook

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've accepted a love letter to be delivered to Anthe.~2|No one could tell it's been read. Could they?~3|The letter has clearly been opened.
Description: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, professing his undying love to one in Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Unopened and pristine~2|Stealthily read~3|Clearly perused
Name: Undercrow: Delivering a Love Letter to Anthe

Description: How does an Almost Dead Man face his end?
Name: Undercrow: Dying Grace

Description: An unsentimental man of pins and the jar, in pursuit of rare lepidopterae.
Name: Undercrow: Incomparable Aurelian

Description: Not so much a corpse as a discarded morning-suit. Nonetheless, his brother at Port Demeaux will want to know.
Name: Undercrow: Lorenzo's Husk

ChangeDescriptionText: 2|There are trespasses to be forgiven.~102|Lorenzo has shed his life, but his light lingers in his friends.~1|You have met an Almost Dead Man in the Undercrow.~3|Saying farewell to a lover in Hideaway.	~5|Delivering a lover's wordless response.	~10|A mercenary in Nook deserves an apology.~15|Delivering a wronged comrade's retribution.~20|A pledge of undying love to one in Anthe.~25|Delivering news of a lover's warm response.~30|Nothing more to be said.~26|Delivering news of a lover's fiery reaction.	~50|The end nears.~100|Lorenzo has shed his life.~110|Lorenzo has shed this life, and his light has been extinguished.
Description: The Almost Dead Man hopes to end a complicated life with a clear conscience.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|There are trespasses to be forgiven.~3|Saying farewell to a lover in Hideaway.~100|Lorenzo has shed this life.~102|Lorenzo has shed this life, but his light lingers in his friends.~1|You have met an Almost Dead Man in the Undercrow.~5|Delivering a lover's wordless response.~10|A mercenary in Nook deserves an apology.~15|Delivering a wronged comrade's retribution.~20|A pledge of undying love to one in Anthe.~25|Delivering news of a lover's warm response.~30|Nothing more to be said.~9|There are trespasses to be forgiven.~19|There are trespasses to be forgiven.~7|Rid of a farewell letter.~17|Rid of an apology letter.~27|Rid of a love letter.~26|Delivering news of a lover's fiery reaction.	.~50|The end nears.~110|Lorenzo has shed this life. Now his companion is due for Adam's Way.
Name: Undercrow: The Almost Dead Man

Description: Safer not to, eh?
Name: Unread Log

Description: He's always watching. He doesn't blink.
Name: Unsettling Sage

Description: A crate of exceptional human souls. It has never known the tender touch of the Imperial Customs stamp. Consequently, it cannot be sold on the open market, and you'd better not be caught with it.
Name: Unstamped Crate of Brilliant Souls

Description: A crate of pleading souls. This one does not bear a customs stamp - it is contraband!
Name: Unstamped Crate of Human Souls

Description: A fruit, a jewel, a tear? Leave that distinction to the botanists. It tastes a little like pine-nuts.
Name: Uttershroom Sporule

Description: You know your way to the Hospital, the Guard-House and Mihir's temple.
Name: Varchas: Directions from the Varchaasi Guard

Description: It's a good thing. Probably?
Name: Varchas: the Agnihotri's Interest

Description: It is hard-earned.
Name: Varchas: The Dour-Faced Nurse's Approval

Description: It seems innocuous enough; what's the worst that could happen?
Name: Varchas: The Jewel-Turbaned Youth's Invitation

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The first Tower-bell has sounded.~2|The second Tower-bell has sounded.~3|The third Tower-bell has sounded.~4|The fourth Tower-bell has sounded.~5|The fifth Tower-bell has sounded: it is evening.~6|It is night, although there is no darkness in Varchas. Time to sleep.~7|Your permitted time in Varchas is over. Time to go; until next time.
Description: Varchas has five mirrored towers. When each has sounded its bell, it is evening.
Name: Varchas: The Knells of the Towers

Description: They worship the sun in Varchas, and have banished darkness from the city.
Name: Varchas: the Mirrored City

Description: Won in bruises and sweat
Name: Varchas: the Respect of the Guard

Description: The brother of the Keeper of the Western Principal Mirror; has a weakness for wine and dark-eyed boys.
Name: Varchas: the Tardy Lamp-Lighter

Description: Speed, stealth, deception. Decreases the range at which enemies will spot you.
Name: Veils

Description: Black, and inscribed with curling symbols.
Name: Venturer's Medallion

Description: Red. As blood tends to be. But redder. Deeper. Alive.
Name: Vial of Highly Questionable Blood

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are smuggling a proscribed cargo of red honey.
Description: Ten marked vials packed in a carefully padded casket. [This stuff is too dangerous even to be properly illegal. Be cautious in taking it to London.]
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Smuggling a proscribed cargo of red honey
Name: Vials of Red Honey

Description: Set it on your binnacle,  feed it the blood of zee-bats. It will guide you.
Name: Vigilant Idol

Description: A knowledge of roles and how they are to be played. [Sometimes, ignorance is freedom. Learning more will have complex effects.]
LevelDescriptionText: 3|Aware of Visitor Roles~4|Aware of Moth Role~7|Aware of Higher Roles
Name: Visage: Expertise in Parts

Description: Taking light into the dark places.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|Empty-handed~3|Carrying a flare and nervous~4|Empty-handed and nervous~5|Carrying a flare and brave~6|Empty-handed and brave~10|Violator of the Sacred Mysteries~1|Carrying a flare~9|Respecter of the Sacred Mysteries~11|Respectful Scholar of the Mysteries~12|Impertinent Scholar of the Mysteries
Name: Visage: Ritual Participant

Description: The role assigned on the island of Visage.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|Unmasked~1|Bat Mask~2|Frog Mask~3|Locust Mask~4|Moth Mask~5|Mask of the Risen Sun
Name: Visage: your Mask

Description: Far above, the Sun remains. [In Venderbight, they're always eager for news of the Surface.]
Name: Vision of the Surface

Description: Vitality and intelligence. What would we do without them? Especially if we're spies, diplomats, or pirates.
Name: Vital Intelligence

Description: Its eyes glitter with awareness. Its melancholy has dissipated: now you sense anticipation.
Name: Wakeful Idol

Description: A sinister little squatting image... but its eyes are pleading.
Name: Watchful Curio

Description: WE WILL WORK. WE WILL ONLY WORK. [This trio of Clay stokers will reduce crew requirements, but also crew capacity, and will slightly increase engine power. They are fitted to an Auxiliary slot. When they are not in use, they will stand, patiently, hands by their sides, flat grey eyes unreadable. One will say, sometimes: "I LIKE IT WHEN IT IS QUIET."]
Name: WE ARE CLAY

Description: Blood oozes slowly from the flesh around it, and is drawn into the scar.
Name: Weeping Scar

Description: "Oh yes, the Drowned Man is humming tonight, a song in the water like the bones of fish."
Name: Whispering Trophy-Case

Description: Speak the right phrase, and the tumblers will align and unlock it. But what is the right phrase? [The Alarming Scholar may have some ideas.]
Name: Whisper-Locked Puzzle-Box

AvailableAt: Available for one Scintillack at the Fathomking's Hold; counteracts illusion at Dahut.
Description: It is said you may eat it if you ever need to break an illusion at Dahut. But be cautious.
Name: White Mollyflower

Description: Glass as clear as ice and sharp as salt.
Name: Whithern Optical

Description: She knows the uses of fire. But she's not cut out for the zee. Take her to London, and the Brass Embassy.
Name: Wistful Deviless

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You witnessed the Curator's Emergence
Description: "...tomb-colonists do not exactly die. Many end in the Grand Sanatorium, withering slowly to insensate horror. (This is not publicised.) A few end in Emergence: transformation to a flimsy thing of wings and knowledge, an end in ecstacy, the delight of becoming an egg, of sorts. This is accounted a grand and vile and tempting sin..."
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You witnessed the Curator's Emergence
Name: Witnessed: the Curator's End

Description: You have told a truth that cuts deep.
Name: Wounding Truth

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You're going to Port Carnelian.~2|You're going to Polythreme.~3|You're going to Port Cavendish.
Description: You cannot allow the Wreckers to claim innocents. Particularly innocents that may pay for their warning.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Port Carnelian~2|Polythreme~3|Port Cavendish
Name: Wrack: A City with Ships to Save

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Fair King has requested you bury your offering of scintillack in Dahut.~5|You buried the scintillack in Dahut. Who knows what it may grow into?	~10|You kept the scintillack for yourself. Who'll ever be the wiser?
Description: When two who are tethered first exchange a gift, the custom is to bury it in Dahut.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Fair King has requested you bury your offering of scintillack in Dahut~5|You buried the scintillack in Dahut. Who knows what it may grow into?~10|You kept the scintillack for yourself. Who'll ever be the wiser?
Name: Wrack: A Wrack Ritual

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Find a jarful of tether in Wrack.~5|Bring the jarful of tether to the Severe Chemist, who waits on the Uttershroom.~10|A satisfied client.~25|A joy forever.
Description: The Severe Chemist wishes to study tether.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Bring the Chemist a jarful of tether from Wrack~5|The Severe Chemist is waiting on the Uttershroom to collect his jarful of tether~10|You delivered the jarful of tether to the Severe Chemist~25|You tasted the tether, instead of delivering it to the Severe Chemist
Name: Wrack: Aiding Research

ChangeDescriptionText: 5|The Fair King will not easily part from his mirror.~10|You may speak to Bourdain on your ship.~15|You have recruited Bourdain.
Description: The Fair King's most treasured possession. Incidentally, it contains the last vestige of Bourdain, who was one of the Seven Against Nidah.
LevelDescriptionText: 5|The Fair King will not easily part from his mirror~10|You may speak to Bourdain on your ship~15|You recruited Bourdain
Name: Wrack: For Want of a Mirror

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You're going to Gaider's Mourn.~2|You're going to Khan's Heart.~3|You're going to the Tomb-Colony of Venderbight.
Description: Go to the port and convince a few captains to zail over Wrack.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Gaider's Mourn~2|Khan's Heart~3|Venderbight
Name: Wrack: New Prey for the Wreckers

ChangeDescriptionText: 2|Are you quite yourself?~1|Do not fear. All shall be well.~3|Your eyes are wider.
Description: Memories are coming to you.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Do not fear. All shall be well~2|Are you quite yourself?~3|Your eyes are wider
Name: Wrack: Remembering

ChangeDescriptionText: 5|There will be something beautiful.
Description: Something might grow in Dahut.
Name: Wrack: Sapphire Blooms

Description: From the very ship you doomed. Offer it in Wrack, and you may taste tether - taste love.
Name: Wrack: Scrap

Description: Your words will sink them into the zee.
Name: Wrack: Ships Sent to Wrack

Description: You have known love. It lingers.
Name: Wrack: Tether Tastings

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The city is in want.~17|The city is thriving!
Description: The wreckers rely on the ships they sink to survive. How are they faring?
LevelDescriptionText: 17|A City of Pleasures	~10|A City that Struggles~13|A City that Survives~1|A City of Want
Name: Wrack: The State of the City

ChangeDescriptionText: 3|You shared a vision of romance with the Fair King.~1|There was a romance.~2|Have you seen something of the Vibrant Lady in the Fair King?
Description: What was, was.
LevelDescriptionText: 3|You shared a vision of romance with the Fair King	~1|You had a vision of a romance~2|Have you seen something of the Vibrant Lady in the Fair King?
Name: Wrack: Visions with the Bone
